title: "AI Expands, Not Compresses"
type: atom
tags:
  - ai
  - thinking
---

Most people use AI to compress information. Rewrite the email faster. Do the requirements in 10 minutes. Repurpose a deck in half an hour.

The real value is in using AI to expand thinking. To give my brain more time on the things that really matter. Opening a chat window and asking AI to generate something from nothing is compression. Pointing AI at a web of my own interconnected thoughts and asking it to stress-test, challenge, and extend is expansion.

AI is a force multiplier. The question is what I'm multiplying.
